<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910315-0045</DOCNO><DOCID>910315-0045.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Mazda Motor Corp.:   Unionized Workers Ratify   Three-Year Labor Contract</HL><DATE>03/15/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A3</SO><CO>   J.MZD LABOR</CO><IN>AUTOMOBILES (AUT)</IN><LP>   Union workers of Mazda Motor Corp. ratified a three-yearpact that boosts their pay to levels for production workersof the Big Three U.S. auto makers.   Mazda officials said workers represented by the UnitedAuto Workers approved the pact by more than a 4-to-1 marginin voting that concluded yesterday. The agreement applies toproduction and skilled trades workers at Mazda's assemblyplant in Flat Rock, Mich.</LP><TEXT>   The accord gives production workers an immediate$1.02-an-hour raise, to $16.65, and raises the hourly pay ofskilled trades workers $1.51 an hour, to $19.34.   The workers also will receive lump-sum payments equal to3% of their wages in the following two years of the pact. Inaddition, Mazda will pay a Christmas bonus of $600 annually,and attendance bonuses of as much as $900 based onperformance. Workers also will benefit from a newprofit-sharing plan.   The prior agreement expired March 2. Mazda is the onlyJapanese auto maker operating an assembly plant in the U.S.</TEXT></DOC>